Great. Just one more clarification. From the DTLS 1.2 Connection ID draft we have the following DTLS header format:
        struct {
            ContentType special_type = tls12_cid;
            ProtocolVersion version;
            uint16 epoch;
            uint48 sequence_number;
            opaque cid[cid_length];               // New field
            uint16 length;
            opaque enc_content[DTLSCiphertext.length];
        } DTLSCiphertext;

            Figure 3: DTLS 1.2 CID-enhanced Ciphertext Record.

So the packet formatting is epoch/seqnum/CID/length.
In the DTLS 1.3 Figure 4 we have the following unified header format: CID/ compressed seqnum/length.

Do we have an interoperability issue here for Connection ID between DTLS 1.2 and 1.3 header formats?

Regards
Andy

